        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Expose skill long-description data on the v1 skill list/detail payloads.\n- Add conservative `metadata.setup` entries derived from parsed manifest requirements.\n- Populate list descriptions from the real `latestVersionSummary`/digest path and read GitHub-backed detail descriptions from cached `githubSkillContents`.\n- Update public schema packages and add regression coverage for list/detail API output.\n\nFixes #2570.\n\n## Setup metadata contract\n\nThis version intentionally narrows `metadata.setup[]` to the minimum useful public contract:\n\n```json\n{ \"key\": \"HA_TOKEN\", \"required\": true }\n```\n\nIt does **not** expose `target`, inferred `type`, generated `label`, `help`, or placeholder fields. That keeps the first release from turning heuristic credential-storage or UI decisions into a stable public API. Downstream clients can prompt for the listed keys, but env-vs-config storage and field rendering remain client-side policy until maintainers approve a richer setup schema.\n\n`required` is true for entries sourced from `requires.env` / `requires.config`; `envVars[]`-only declarations follow their `required` flag.\n\n## Behavior proof\n\nLocal HTTP proof was run against this branch through the real `convex/httpApiV1.ts` exported handlers with fixture-backed Convex action context.\n\n- Public v1 list endpoint includes `description` plus conservative `metadata.setup`:\n\n```bash\ncurl -s 'http://127.0.0.1:52160/api/v1/skills?limit=1'\n```\n\nResult shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"items\": [\n    {\n      \"slug\": \"home-assistant\",\n      \"description\": \"Long-form frontmatter description for the catalog list.\",\n      \"metadata\": {\n        \"setup\": [\n          { \"key\": \"HA_TOKEN\", \"required\": true },\n          { \"key\": \"HA_URL\", \"required\": true }\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"nextCursor\": null\n}\n```\n\n- Hosted skill detail uses full `SKILL.md` markdown for `skill.description` and the same conservative setup shape:\n\n```bash\ncurl -s http://127.0.0.1:52160/api/v1/skills/home-assistant\n```\n\nResult shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"skill\": {\n    \"slug\": \"home-assistant\",\n    \"description\": \"# Home Assistant\\n\\nFull SKILL.md setup instructions.\"\n  },\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"setup\": [\n      { \"key\": \"HA_TOKEN\", \"required\": true },\n      { \"key\": \"HA_URL\", \"required\": true }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n- GitHub-backed skill detail with no hosted `latestVersionId` uses cached `githubSkillContents` markdown:\n\n```bash\ncurl -s http://127.0.0.1:52160/api/v1/skills/aiq-deploy\n```\n\nResult shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"skill\": {\n    \"slug\": \"aiq-deploy\",\n    \"description\": \"# AIQ Deploy\\n\\nLong GitHub-backed README from githubSkillContents.\"\n  },\n  \"latestVersion\": null,\n  \"owner\": { \"handle\": \"nvidia\" }\n}\n```\n\nNo secret values are exposed.\n\n## Tests\n\n- `bunx vitest run convex/httpApiV1.handlers.test.ts convex/skills.publicListCursor.test.ts packages/schema/src/schemas.test.ts packages/clawhub/src/schema/schemas.test.ts`\n- `bun run format:check -- convex/httpApiV1/skillsV1.ts convex/httpApiV1.handlers.test.ts packages/schema/src/schemas.ts packages/clawhub/src/schema/schemas.ts`\n- `bunx tsc --noEmit`\n- `bunx tsc -p packages/schema/tsconfig.json --noEmit && bunx tsc -p packages/clawhub/tsconfig.json --noEmit`\n- `bun run lint`\n",
        "branch": "codex/api-skill-description-setup",
